    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <pb/>
                <opener>
                    <dateline><lb/>Zurich, Switzerland<lb/>April 10th, at night</dateline>
                    <salute><lb/>Carson, child my beloved,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p><lb/>you know that, leaving the day after tomorrow,
                    <lb/>feeling half-afraid and proud, leaving behind
                    <lb/>me all I care for, once again, + a wave of love, --
                    <lb/>yesterday, talking to a really good friend about
                    <lb/>America, -- explaining why I wrote a most critical
                    <lb/>+ terribly serious article on Chaplin's "Great Dictator",
                    <lb/>-- explaining, painting the entire profound horror of
                    <lb/>Disney's Fantasia, -- I was quite desperate, but found
                    <lb/>myself in the end breaking out in one enthousiastic feeling
                    <lb/>+ belief in the U. S. being not better [...]</p>
                <p><lb/>I remembered you manuscript, + felt bitter [...]</p>
                <pb/>
                <p><lb/>This was like a symbol [...]</p>
